claim: Cell- and egg-based flu vaccines have the potential to develop mutations during production, which may reduce their effectiveness.
explanation: Header of a journal article from the journal "Vaccine" showing the Elsevier logo, journal name, homepage URL, and a partial cut-off of the article title text. The image contains only the journal header and partial article title with no data or statements regarding cell- or egg-based flu vaccine production mutations or their impact on effectiveness, and therefore does not support the claim.
